<html><head><title>Upcoming Update</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Upcoming Update</h3><p>The next scheduled update for EverQuest is planned for October 26, 2005. Here are some of the things that are currently planned:<ul>  <li>New Default UI Skin </li>  <li>Modifications to DoD Missions &amp; Loot </li>  <li>EverQuest will now use the Operating System's mouse so players can easily go between applications while in windowed mode </li>  <li>Take a look at Kithicor for some holiday fun </li>  <li>Players will have the ability to make their helms invisible </li>  <li>Improved controls in the guild bank </li>  <li>New command for opening a web browser from the game command prompt </li>  <li>New Audio Triggers command </li>  <li>Fix for the Pet HP for items </li>  <li>Fix for the loss of mana/HP while zoning </li></ul>Please join the Test server to see some of the changes.</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Wednesday, 19 October, 2005<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=11986">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=11986</a><br>Printed On: Tue Dec 20 4:15:42 PST 2005<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>